-- Mexico Stocks: Grupo Elektra, Desarrolladora Homex, Asur Gain
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2012-01-04T22:17:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-04/mexico-stocks-grupo-elektra-desarrolladora-homex-asur-gain.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Mexico trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading.  The IPC  index (MEXBOL)  was little changed at 37,387.63  Mexico’s consumer confidence index may have climbed to 92.5
in December from 89.5 the previous month, economists surveyed by
Bloomberg forecast before a report due Jan. 6.  Grupo Elektra SA (ELEKTRA*)  , the retail and banking
company controlled by billionaire  Ricardo Salinas , rose 0.6
percent to 1,425.82 pesos.  Desarrolladora Homex SAB (HOMEX*)  ,
Mexico’s largest homebuilder, rose 3 percent to 40.67 pesos.  Grupo Aeroportuario del Sureste SAB (ASURB)  , the
operator of airports in southern Mexico, rose 2.8 percent to
80.06 pesos. Passenger traffic increased 15.3 percent in
December from the same month last year, the company said today
in a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
